name: Kevin Campbell
summary: Former Arsenal and Everton striker Kevin Campbell passed away at the age of 54 following a short illness. Campbell played for both clubs during his career, scoring 98 goals in 282 appearances. He was known for his physicality, aerial ability, and goal-scoring prowess. Campbell also played for Bradford City, Nottingham Forest, and Leyton Orient. The football community has expressed sadness and condolences over his passing.
